Commercial Bank of Zimbabwe Issues 3-Year $50 Million Bond, Herald Reports

-- B y   G o d f r e y   M a r a w a n y i k a
-- 
2011-07-06T09:06:14Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-06/commercial-bank-of-zimbabwe-issues-3-year-50-million-bond-herald-reports.html
Commercial Bank of Zimbabwe Ltd.
issued $50 million of three-year bonds on the Cayman Stock
Exchange, the Herald reported.  The bonds were arranged and guaranteed by African Export-
Import Bank, the Harare-based state-controlled newspaper cited
Andrew Carey, who advised AfreximBank on the transaction, as
saying. The money will probably be used to finance
infrastructure investments, the Herald said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Gordon Bell at 
 gbell16@bloomberg.net  